  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The effect of use of the microflare down regulation protocol on the outcome of the IVF/ICSI
      cycles in poor responders
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The microflare as a method of down regulation protocol can be used to prepare the females
      suffering from poor ovarian reserve to undergo IVF/ICSI cycles. In this study we are trying
      to outline its effect on the clinical pregnancy rate as a main primary outcome, and to
      compare its use with the addition of growth hormone to the same protocol.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
